Prep the ingredients: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. In a #small pot{}, bring @water{1%cup} with a large @salt{pinch} to a boil. Zest and halve the @lime{1}. Cut one half into wedges. Halve, peel, and finely chop the @shallot{1%2oz}(peeled and finely chopped). Halve the @grape tomatoes{4%oz}.

Cook the quinoa: Add the @quinoa{1/2%cup} to the boiling water, cover, and reduce to a low simmer for ~{15-20%minutes}, until tender. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Make the wasabi aioli: in a #small bowl{}, combine the @mayonnaise{1.8%oz}, lime zest, a squeeze of lime (to taste) and the @wasabi paste{1%tsp} (to taste). Season with salt and pepper.

Make the panko crust: In a #medium pan{}, melt 1 @butter{1%tbsp}. Toss the @panko breadcrumbs{1/2%cup} into the melted butter and season with salt and pepper. Transfer the panko to a #plate{} and wipe out the pan.

Cook the mahi mahi: Season the @mahi-mahi{12%oz} on all sides with salt and pepper. Spread the top of each fillet with 1 teaspoon of wasabi aioli. Press the panko onto the top of each fillet and place onto a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Bake in the oven for about ~{10%minutes}, until flaky and opaque.

Saute the green beans and tomatoes: Meanwhile, heat 1 @butter{1%tbsp} in the same pan over medium heat. Add the shallot and @green beans{4%oz} and cook, tossing, for ~{4-5%minutes}, until the shallots are softened. Add a splash of @?water{} to the pan and let the green beans steam until tender. Add the tomatoes and cook, tossing, for another ~{1-2%minutes}, until heated through. Season with salt and pepper.

Plate: Serve the panko-crusted mahi mahi on a bed of veggies and quinoa. Serve with the remaining wasabi aioli and a wedge of lime. Enjoy!